 Gavel PHOTO:Getty Images  The Magistrate, Mrs Mary Awodele, ordered that Adekunle should remain in Ilesa custodial centre pending the hearing of the case.
She, thereafter, adjourned the case till July 14. The defendant, whose address was not provided, is facing a two-count of assault. Earlier, the Prosecutor, ASP Fagboyinbo Abiodun, had told the court that the defendant committed the offence on May 25, at 1.30 pm. at Okinni area of Osogbo. Abiodun said that the defendant used his cigarette to burn his old son all over his body for unjust reasons. He said that the offence contravened Sections 355 and 33 (1) and (2) of the Criminal Law of Osun, 2002. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .